net.proteusframework.core.locale

Class LocalizedObjectKey

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.core.locale.LocalizedObjectKey
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, TextSource
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TransientLocalizedObjectKey

    public class LocalizedObjectKey
extends Object
implements Serializable, TextSource, Cloneable
    Wrapper class for the benefit of identifying the objects that are LocalizedObject keys.
    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@i2rd.com)

      • copyLocalizedObjectKey

        @Nullable
public static LocalizedObjectKey copyLocalizedObjectKey(LocaleSource localeSource,
                                                                  @Nullable
                                                                  LocalizedObjectKey keyToCopy)
        Copies the given LocalizedObjectKey values into a new key for all used locales. The use case is for copying a key that may have text values in multiple locales. The new key will be stored in the specified locale source. If the key is static, this will still create a new key. If the key to copy is null, this will return null.
        Parameters:
        localeSource - the locale source
        keyToCopy - the key to copy. may be null.
        Returns:
        the new key

      • createCopy

        public LocalizedObjectKey createCopy()
        Creates a copy for the TextSource interface. This does not copy the localizations. Use copyLocalizedObjectKey(LocaleSource, LocalizedObjectKey) for that. Create a copy of the text source if necessary.
        Specified by:
        createCopy in interface TextSource
        Returns:
        a new instance with the same key and symbolic name.

        public static void delete(LocaleSource ls,

        Delete the specified key. This will remove all localizations for non-static keys. If an error occurs, then it is logged.
        Parameters:

        key - the key. May be null.

      • getKey

 @Contract(value="null->null")
public static Object getKey(Object key)

        Returns:
        the key.

      • getLocalizedObjectKey

        public static LocalizedObjectKey getLocalizedObjectKey(LocaleSource localeSource,
                                                       Locale locale,
                                                       @Nullable
                                                       LocalizedObjectKey key,
                                                       String text)
        Get an updated localized object key for the specified text. If the key doesn't exist, it is stored in the specified LocaleSource. If the key is static, a new key is created.

        Typical usage:

        myEntity.setLOKProperty(LocalizedObjectKey.getLocalizedObjectKey( localeSource, Locale.ENGLISH, myEntity.getLOKProperty(), newText));

        Parameters:
        localeSource - the locale source.
        locale - the locale.
        key - the existing key. May be null.
        text - the text to update.
        Returns:
        the key.
